<p>The TRADOC Commanding General, Gen. Robert Cone, and Chief of Staff of the Army, Gen. Ray Odierno, tasked Army Experimentation to assess the functional integration of future Army initiatives to help shape the Army of 2020 and beyond.  Simultaneous and complex design changes have been integrated into Army-level experiments across Joint Campaign Phases 0-IV.  During each phase of the operation, running estimates are maintained to isolate critical design changes which result in new planning considerations and employment capabilities.  The end state is a functionally integrated collection of observations, insights and recommendations across the DOTMLPF spectrum that, to date, have developed evolving future Army doctrine, identified non-resident, atrophied and new training skills, and will recommend improvements to future Army force design.   The culminating event will be conducted by Eighth Army, who will "bench test" the DOTMLPF solutions during its December Mission Command Training Program Warfighter Exercise in order to help shape the future Army.</p>
<p class="BubbleTitleSection">REBALANCING THE ARMY</p>
<p>As the Army redesigns to a smaller end-strength, experimentation will play a critical role in ensuring that we have the right capabilities and force mix to be operationally effective.  More importantly, it will ensure the Army invests in the capabilities it will need instead of what is merely available.</p>
<p class="BubbleTitleSection">About Concept Development and Learning Directorate</p>
<p>The JAED Division, part of the Concept Development and Learning Directorate, leads, manages and synchronizes Army experiments to support current and future developments in support of the Soldier.</p>
